						<summary>

						<p>Pāṇḍya, Jaṭāvarman Sundarapāṇḍya, 12th year = c. 14th Century.</p>						

						<p>A Pāṇḍiyarāyaṉ seems to have sought protection <hi rend="italic">(āsariyam)</hi> from the god of Tirukkuṉṟākkuḍi-uḍaiya-nāyiṉār and (the nāḍu of) Iraṇḍumalai-nāḍu, for which he gifted his dues <hi rend="italic">(rēkai)</hi> from <hi rend="italic">arasu-sutandiram</hi> of some locality to the temple.</p>						

						</summary>
